editorial_summary.overview: Eatery with a bustling patio & bright, snug interior, serving classic Mexican fare & margaritas.

formatted_address: 277 Augusta Ave, Toronto, ON M5T 2L7, Canada
name: El Trompo

reviews.text: You literally could not get more authentic Mexican food than this. The patio is nice, but I personally enjoy sitting inside - it's like being invited over to eat at a family friend's house than being at a restaurant. Service is friendly, personal and absolutely delightful. Food is fairly priced and generously portioned. I recommend the Jamaica and Horchatta drinks for something light and refreshing. There's nothing negative I can say about my experience here!!
Authentic Mexican food with an absolutely delicious taste! The margaritas were tasty and the tacos were fantastic. I will definitely be back and recommend to others.

Fish tacos are my one true love and el trompo did not disappoint! fresh ingredients and a well balanced taco! Plus their cute patio and drinks make it a great experience. Go early because the patio will fill up fast!

great little spot for food! came in on a saturday afternoon just walking around and was super fast & great service. got the el pastor and mushroom tacos for something small for fuel to walk around but was surprisingly filling. would def recommend trying it out since they had a great menu and amazing service!

I was missing the authentic taste of my home country 🇲🇽, this place was a great find. During the weekends there is live entertainment with a singer/violinist in the afternoon 👏🏼About the food, I started with a choriqueso, then tried tacos al pastor and cochinita tacos, the prices are awesome, the service is super fast, I even tried the flan and some café de olla, everything was delicious. I wish I could have more lemon without having to pay for it.

editorial_summary.overview: Susur Lee's stylish eatery for creative Asian & French-influenced dishes meant for sharing.

formatted_address: 601 King St W, Toronto, ON M5V 1M5, Canada
name: Lee

reviews.text:
This is a restaurant I've always wanted to try! Luckily I had cousins coming in Toronto and wanted to go to Lee's to celebrate their birthday.

Let me tell you, beginning to end, we were not deceived AT ALL. The quality of service is incredibly amazing, something that I was expecting from this restaurant but they went over my expectations. You don't even notice when their refreshing your plates or refilling your water. We had such an astounding waiter, Conor, he was more than a perfect host. We are glad that we had him serving us. He knew the menu detailed to the bone.

We were a group of 5 and chose to do the "Chef's Choice", I believe that's what its called... We give them a price and they are able to choose your menu. More like a surprise 3 course menu concept. We had so much food that we were all so full at the end that we were scared we wouldn't have any space for dessert. Such a great experience.

We came here after hearing great things about the restaurant. To our excitement this restaurant did not disappoint, everything we had was delicious and I had zero complaints. It's best if you share your food here as opposed to individually getting your own meals, as you can try more dishes. I was skeptical about the Singapore style slaw at first as I'm not a fan of regular slaw but it was amazing! It was fresh and full of flavours, 20 ingredients to be exact. The reviews recommended the cheeseburger spring rolls so we got them and they were definitely worth it as well. I recommend getting the goat cheese tart if you're a fan of olives, cheese and philo pastry because it was delicious as well. The Top Chef curry roasted chicken is a must have, each bite had loads of flavour if you ate it with all the sauces and pineapple too. The servers were very knowledgeable about the food and provided great customer service also. We didn't get the signature sangria so I can't speak to that, but the table beside us did and was complimenting it. I was surprised at the quality in the food because for the same price in many upscale restaurants in Toronto you don't get the same quality in taste. I recommend trying something different on the menu from something you'd normally get at another restaurant because it really is a unique experience. This place is great for a date night! I'd definitely come here again and recommend it for people looking for a unique experience or looking for a restaurant with great food.

Incredible food and drinks that offer a very unique and well-executed take on fusion cuisine.

When ordering, we were given a thorough rundown of the menu by our waiter, however, he went on to talk for a very long time in a manner that felt like a sales pitch. An example of this was him explaining how shared dishes work in unnecessarily extensive detail.

We loved every dish that we ordered. The slaw is a must-have – the presentation was spot on and it tasted fantastic. The other starters we got included the cheeseburger spring rolls which were a really unique idea and tasted great, however, it was a bit watery. The crispy tofu was perfectly seasoned and combined authentic Asian flavours with other more unique flavours that were well executed.

For mains, I'd highly recommend the black cod – the fish was incredibly tender and sweet, pairing well with the sauce and vegetables underneath. We also had the braised beef which was very tender and tasted great with the mushrooms.

It's also worth to try the desserts. The tong yuen were pretty special in stuffing the Chinese dessert with an unconventional hazelnut chocolate inside.

Aside from at the beginning, our waiter was very hospitable and frequently checked up on us. The atmosphere is very lively along with a modern interior that was comfortable to dine in. As a result, is suits a whole variety of different occasions and I'd love to return.

Went to Lee to celebrate my boyfriends bday, the customer service was exceptional. Our favourite is the popular dish, Singaporean salad with 20 ingredients. We got a seasonal alcoholic drink & the Smokey margarita which was both very tasty. We ordered the top chef chicken curry which was the softest chicken we’ve had, the curry was more on the sweet & ginger-y side. We also ordered the fish taco (seasonal), the cheeseburger spring which were both pretty decent compared to the other two dishes we ordered.

Overall, a very good experience! We ended up being really full and maybe would go for 3 dishes next time instead of 4! They even provided a free birthday desert which we really appreciated

My friend and I ate at Lee for Summerlicious. While it was generally good, it wasn’t amazing considering the price. I quite liked the salmon dish and the lobster dish to start. I especially love the Singapore Slaw which is why this is a four star review instead of three.

The servers are great. The patio is decent. I felt that I’ve had curries that were similar in tastiness to the ones at Lee for half the price.

Go and try the slaw!

editorial_summary.overview: Canadian chain selling signature premium-blend coffee, plus light fare like pastries & panini.

formatted_address: 438 University Ave, Toronto, ON M5G 2K8, Canada
name: Tim Hortons

reviews.text: I love this Tim Hortons. The staff here are very kind and very friendly and the service is quick and accurate. I’ve been to this location several times and I don’t ever recall the staff getting my order wrong. I’ve always been very happy with the quality of my drinks here. The staff here are very patient and they really do a great job!

This store is located in a convenient location. Just outside the St. Patrick station. The staff is friendly. Mostly clean. I am satisfied with the quality of drinks. The reason I did not give all 5 stars is sometimes the service is too slow. It's understandable that servers are tired at the end of the day and are slower, but serving only 2 people in 10 mins is not okay when there are more than 6 people in line. Hope they change that.

In store is usually fine but I almost never get the right order when I order for delivery. I just had the worst one. We got 1.5/6 items. Literally missing two coffees, two cookies, the bun that goes with the soup. I'm surprised the soup was even the right one. This location has just gone downhill recently.

I had left my large coffee for a while to go to the washroom n the tim employee threw it away but when i came back he remembered and gave me back a medium one. Very prudent no drama environment. They don't give out receipts unless you ask tough and also did not have cinnamon for the drinks i loved the pumpkin seeds& spice doughnuts n drinks. Please bring back all year sugar free if u can. Decaff coffee is amazing with almond milk. Good vegan option please have more

A good place to grab a cup of tea 🍵 or coffee before heading to work. Staff is efficient and service is quick.
Four stars awarded because there is nothing so good that cannot be improved.

editorial_summary.overview: Vietnamese quick-serve restaurant with a health focus that's open late for noodles & sandwiches.

formatted_address: 546 Church St, Toronto, ON M4Y 2EI, Canada
name: Ginger

reviews.text:
Fair food with fair price.
Service is not as expected.
Location wise is very convenient. I don’t sure if I will visit them again, because the food they serve is huge amount of carb with very little vegetable and very little portion of meat.
Delicious, one of my favorite spots in Toronto! Love the staff too! Thank you❤️ I love getting the assorted meat, seafood and mixed veggies on crispy noodles.

I would give it -5 stars if I could.

The restaurant itself is full of flies that constantly hover over you.
Banh mi sandwiches weren’t horrible but not great either. Too much sauce leaving them soggy, not enough cilantro or veggies.
The worst item the pad Thai, do not get this !!

It was like a spaghetti noodle drenched in what tasted like plum sauce. When I told the cashier it was bad she could care less. Didn’t say sorry, took the plate and walked away.
The only decent part of it was the chicken which is the only part eaten in the photo. Honestly avoid this place. Don’t waste your $$

It’s ok. I got there Popular Dish there. It’s Beef, Chicken & Shrimp with White Rice & a Spring Roll. I don’t eat Shrimp so I got it without it. It was ok tho..They was cheap on the meat..The Chicken was So Thin…They could of gave me a little more Seeing that I don’t eat Seafood…I would of gave them a 4 Star, but because of that reason they get a 3 1/2 Star
Decent Vietnamese fare, when looking for something quick and cheap. Though prices are not what they used to be. Also it’s best take out here, the dine-in experience isn’t exactly tantalizing.

editorial_summary.overview: Fast-food outlet serving up namesake root beer, plus burgers, chicken & fries.

formatted_address: 500 Bloor St W, Toronto, ON M5S 1Y3, Canada
name: A&W Canada

reviews.text: A&W has been the most consistent of the fast food places lately. The food and the customer service is way better than Tim's and McDonald's combined. The people at every location I've visited has been respectful and the food is prepared properly, great taste and presentation. The gentleman behind the counter is top notch. Cheers to a good morning

The food may be good, but the kitchen workers were fully gripping the sandwiches with their bare hands. I really enjoyed their onion rings, but the lack of hand washing has put me off indefinitely. Nasty

I stopped here after a meeting in the area. It was a small location but had about 5 tables and a few bar seats. It's really small and I'm not a fan of big name fast food restaurants having very small locations.

The staff tried to get the tables clean but as expected it was fairly busy so they were always having to go back to the counter to take orders.

The washroom was closed as is most washrooms on Bloor St West. The food was great, the fries were fresh, the burger was good and they had the cooled mugs which some places don't do as much these days.

The issue is the customers, either students or the people who live or visit the area are extremely sloppy and dirty.
They will order a bunch of stuff and literally leave the tables full. It happens at other places on Bloor St West too like Popeye's, Starbucks etc ...

The staff can't keep up in small location only so many can safely stay behind the counter, if you want these small locations in your area to need to chip in and make sure you clean AFTER YOURSELF. Why were you not taught manners?

Tonight I experienced the worst "Fast Food" Experience I've ever had in my life. I waited 27 minutes for a mama burger and onion rings. Which I had to ask the lady working where my order was before she gave it to me. And it might have been the coldest burger I've ever ate when I finally got to eat it. Do yourself a favor and NEVER go here.

This is by far the slowest location. I've been here multiple times and they are always taking their time, and there's usually 2 people max working. The food is good but if you're in a rush don't bother.

editorial_summary.overview: Intimate eatery for Eritrean & Ethiopian eats, with vegan & gluten-free options & a coffee ceremony.

formatted_address: 977 Bloor St W, Toronto, ON M6H 1L8, Canada
name: African Palace

reviews.text: Food was fantastic! So flavourful and filling. It doesn't look like it would be filling but it really is. I have a very heavy accent so there was a slight issue with ordering gluten free but it was fixed straight away. Would absolutely eat here again!

Tasty meal. The owner of the restaurant is quite nice.

However though: they need a hand wash stand somewhere within the main floor so people aren’t going to the basement to wash their hands before and after a meal.

Super cute Ethiopian Resturant. They have vegan & gluten free options. The food is delicious, although you eat with your hands. The coffee ceremony is a MUST if you like coffee.
Great service and friendly staff.

Our first time dining in a restaurant since the beginning of the pandemic was a great experience. The staff here was so friendly (and sweet with our 2 year-old) and the food was delicious. We all really enjoyed it. We have been missing the homey feel of family run restaurants and are happy to have found this spot in the west end. We will definitely be back!

I've been coming here for at least 15 years...
A first glance the decor is basic, like and other restaurant really but the food is phenomenal and the vibes are on point. It felt like we were being welcomed into someone's home. The server was patient with us and even gave us a cultural experience of feeding one another. Thank you for sharing, we love it!

editorial_summary.overview: Relaxed, contemporary restaurant serving Thai & Malaysian dishes, plus beer & wine.

formatted_address: 243 Carlton St., Toronto, ON M5A 2L2, Canada
name: Thai Room - Cabbagetown

reviews.text: Food was good here! The presentation has improved a lot! The pad Thai was decent this time around. It was a bit more sour then expected, I believe they had put too much tamarind in this one. Used to be just perfect! If you got one with the right amount of sauce, you got some good pad Thai 🙏🏼

The food used to taste better before. Not sure if they went through management/chef change but it doesn't have the authentic Thai taste anymore. Ambiance is nice. Watch out not to tip twice, the bill already includes a 20% gratuity but the machine still prompts for a tip!
I had 3 different kinds of fried rice here twice - chicken, egg and vegetables. All 3 are really tasty. Takes me back to street food in India. Scrumptious and look great too. Highly recommend.

Good value and tasty food. Thank you Thai room for delivering delicious food.
Edited review : again we got hot delicious vegan food delivered home.

WARNING ! : ketchup in the padthai

The “traditional” pad thai is “tomato based” as described by the worker, it tastes like ketchup and noodles😂. This is a joke, I just ordered for the 2 for 1 deal and the portions are good, the quality however is lacking. I did not pay 30 bucks for some noodles and ketchup I don’t recommend.

editorial_summary.overview: Pizzeria offering thin-crust, regular & multi-grain pies with a wide selection of toppings.

formatted_address: 787 Bathurst St, Toronto, ON M5S 0B7, Canada
name: Panago Pizza

reviews.text: Delicious pizza and very clean location, though I would've preferred a bit more veggie toppings. You can tell it's made fresh! I also appreciate how they cut the slices in 6 rather than 4 for a personal size pizza. Overall a very pleasant experience and would go again.

Updated review: Monday, Jan 16th 2023.

Pizza was good. But the staff is too loud and they don't use gloves in making and handling the food.  So they need to improve on that.

Old review.
Cheese pizza was good. Good customer service.

I am not a pizza person, but I cannot resist stopping by this place. Their pizza is fresh and of very high quality. The dough is really good and amount of ingredients is generous. The taste is balanced. Highly recommend.
Excellent service! The pizza is always so yummy. Great variety of topping. We ordered  14 large pizzas for a school event and everyone was super happy with their food.

Ran across this amazing place at Bloor and Bathrust. Quick service, friendly staff, great options for meat, veggie, chicken and Vegan lovers. What made the pizza place unique is you get to modify, create your own , half n half's.. I really enjoyed my time here and will be visiting again for sure!

editorial_summary.overview: Stalwart 1930s bistro reborn under chef Noah Goldberg decorated with arresting wall tapestries.

formatted_address: 373 Queen St W, Toronto, ON M5V 2A4, Canada
name: Peter Pan Bistro

reviews.text: Went for a work dinner here with some coworkers, we were a decent sized group, I think 8 or 9 of us. They were super conscious of covid protocols which was comforting because some of my coworkers were concerned. Food was so delicious and our wine pairings were lovely. This place is kind of a Toronto staple and I've never been! Was super pleased with my experience will definitely try to return again and enjoy their patio in the warmer months. They have a two level patio!

It was my first time at this restaurant, and I was very impressed with their food.

Their meals are very different from the traditional brunch, so it's a pleasant surprise to get the feed.  This time I ordered the classic breakfast (although it wasn't traditional), and my friend ordered the mushroom omelette.
My traditional breakfast consists of three slices of bread, two eggs, a small salad, a very, very tasty hash brown, and optional side dishes (I chose smoked salmon).
Their hash browns are shaped like fish cakes, thicker than regular hash browns and round shapes.  It's very crispy outside, and the potato inside is excellent.  I also love their smoked salmon, which is very satisfying.  Their meals are small in size, more like small and delicate meals.  My friend also loves her omelettes.

I like the ambience and setting of the restaurant, and the overall feeling is very comfortable.  It's just that part of the space is very noisy, so it's hard to converse with friends.  The servers are friendly and smiley.  The food is delicious; the portions are small compared to the price, which is not cheap.  However, they have their delicious specialties, so I'll be visiting again.

Just had dinner there and a bottle of wine with my husband yesterday. The meals were good! However I always care about a really good service and they delivered impeccable customer care! We had ordered a chocolate souffle that was unfortunately undercooked but upon our remark, they didn't hesitate to offer us a brand new chocolate soufflé and a coffee on them, free of charge due to their kitchen mistake! If you like smaller restaurant with a more low-key comfort vibe this is a good place to try!

This is for me one of the top restaurants that I have tried in Toronto. The taste of the food is amazing. We went for brunch around 1pm without any reservation and we were served quickly. Friendly staff and nice atmosphere. Egg Benedict was my favorite the hollandaise sauce was great.

The Peter Pan Bistro is a delicious and lovely place to eat. The interior is filled with these lovely carpet-covered animal heads which give the place a unique style.

I had the burger which was great and my mom had the salmon which was next level. Delicious and tasted fresh.

The prices are a bit high, but arguably worth it for the great taste and location. Definitely more of a fine dining experience.

editorial_summary.overview: Basic, unassuming spot cooking up spicy tofu hot pots & other Korean fare, including kimchi.

formatted_address: 691 Bloor St W, Toronto, ON M6G 1L3, Canada
name: Buk Chang Dong Soon Tofu

reviews.text: Went here with my family and was thoroughly impressed. To begin, the atmosphere is quaint, but nice. The restaurant feels a little cramped, but that's really looking at the devil in the details. Overall, the food was excellent with a strong balance of flavours. From the house staple Soon Tofu to the Spicy Pork each dish was crafted well and had deep flavour profiles. As a heads up, each main course comes with side dishes (kimchi, bean sprouts, beans). For service, the waitress was extremely welcoming and provided top-level service. However, the guy up front was a little rude, but we looked past that because of the overall service and quality of the food. All in all, a great restaurant that you have to try.

Very busy restaurant. When I arrived on a Saturday evening, I had to wait a little bit for a table to free up. It was not very long though. Service was quick. Their specialty are the tofu soups. They serve it with rice in a stone bowl and some small side dishes. You can crack an egg and add it yourself in your bowl so that it will slowly cook. It was nice and warm. You can chose your level of spicyness. We got the dumpling beef one as well as the vegetable one. They were very good and served hot. The rice was really good. It was a lot of food for me and I could not finish the rice. On weekends and holidays, they don’t split bills so only one person can pay. You can get 10% with takeout only. They have washrooms downstairs. I like that there are hand sanitizers on the tables.

We were in the area and looking for some Korean food. This place is good for a quick sit down and go. It was a bit cold, I think the heat setting was on low. Other than that the food was amazing! We enjoyed dumplings, tofu and kimchi versions of soon tofu. Nice filling meal and good value 👍🏼

A nice little Korean restaurant with limited but tasty menu.  The good is good, but the portions are ungenerous and small compare to similar Korean restaurants.  This is probably the only Korean restaurant that I am aware with such small portions on everything, from appetizers to main dishes.

The beef plate was very tasty, not over seasoned and they’re generous with the portions. I didn’t end up with more rice than needed. The gamja-tang isn’t the best you can get in Korea town, but it’s a solid standard. The cutlet was also solid, but not really worth it in my opinion. Could use more sides!

It’s a well known chain for a reason. Their location in North York is fantastic too.

editorial_summary.overview: Cafe offering chocolate desserts (from waffles to fondue) & drinks made with a variety of cocoas.

formatted_address: 28 Gristmill Lane, Toronto, ON M5A 3C4, Canada
name: CACAO 70 Eatery (Distillery)

reviews.text:
I ordered an espresso, Tiramisu cake, cheese cake and brownie cake.

I was pretty late and got there when they were about to close. I had to do take out because of that, but we were able to sit outside the cafe. They have a nice outdoor area, which I enjoyed.

My favourite was the cheesecake because it had whipped cream and raspberry topping. I would come back provided I get to sit inside :)

This place is amazing for all of you chocolate lovers! They have a great selections of chocolate (white, dark, milk, mix, etc.) and you can customize your drinks or order according to your preference. The portion size is pretty generous and it is recommended to order the sharing plate. The chocolate fondue is one of their signature dish that I highly recommend. If it's your first time, I would suggest Cacao 70 Signature Hot Chocolate. It's almost double the price of the regular hot chocolate, but it is served on a cool glassware glazed with chocolate, and you get to mix the drink yourself.

The service was great even though it was very busy in the evening and there were a long lines. Despite that, the staffs were able to deliver excellent service and get our order quickly. This place is great for all occasion, whether it is a date, hangout with friends, or for family. It is, after all, very cozy and has a good vibes.

I went here on Monday with my boyfriend for our date. It was so cold that day so we decided to go inside this place to warm us up and eat before we continued strolling around the city.

The place is so spacious and neat! We had a meat lover omelette meal, mini fruits + chocolate dip, and hot chocolate. Everything was so good! We enjoyed and had a great time. The employees are so friendly as well. The experience was 10/10, definitely recommend to come by this place and get your sweet addiction on!

Wandered into this cafe on a cold Sunday morning walk through the distillery district. Immediately we were greeted and after a quick scan of the menu we opted for an amazing breakfast sandwich, grilled cheese and hot chocolate and a cacao 70 signature mocha. Everything was great! Service was fast and the area spacious and clean. The signature 70 mocha was delicious!!! Try it! Thank you for a very nice experience!

One of the many fun spots to hit up in the Distillery district. We stopped in to get out of the cold and this was a very fun way to warm up. Tried the Cacao Blast (milk chocolate), the Cacao 70 Factory Hot Chocolate (dark chocolate) and 2 churro donuts - the coffee and the chocolate peanut butter. The photos probably won't go justice to how good the experience is. For those that love chocolate, this place is an absolute must!

editorial_summary.overview: This minimally decorated eatery offers a simple menu of burgers, fried chicken sandwiches & fries.

formatted_address: 619 College St, Toronto, ON M6G 1B5, Canada
name: Rudy

reviews.text:
The smashed patties are always crispy on the edges and super juicy, and I love that the burgers are consistently picture perfect!

Our fries came late which wasn't a big deal but they were nice enough to comp us with a brownie (which is now my favourite brownie in town). Thank you!! :))

Going to Toronto to explore and my first food stop to try is RUDY burger on College Street :) They do looks like they have an amazing burgers selection. The lady that works there highly recommend Valentino burger but they are huge !!! Lol and I plan to visit at least 10 food places on that day lol so I try their basic RUDY burger and it was absolutely delicious!!! Never in my life I ate a crunchy beef patties !! This burger is absolutely delicious and satisfying !! Just look at how beautiful the burger looks like and yum yum yum delicious !!

Its a decent tasting burger but cmon look at the size of the thing... What I would expect in a McDonald's. It's not much bigger than the gravy cup beside it.

The patty has taken 'smash burger' to a new extreme, to the point where there was barely any meat in an already small burger.

First time here and I work down the street but unfortunately don't think I would try it again after this experience

RUDY does something that not many in the burger business do (but should): they care about the bread. So RUDY's hamburgers are not just "a safe bet" amidst a congregation of poorly designed and love-lacking burgers; you do have to try them out because they're delicious and the best burgers I've had in Toronto. The meat is juicy, the bread is fresh and everything in between is well-balanced.

The service is decent but the system they have for taking your order and then delivering it (dine-in) seems a bit clunky: the cashier going out to call the names of people that he can't find, bags left on the counter without apparent owner, orders taking too long to be prepared (i had to check with them for mine)... it can improve but i'm mostly calling out the system and not the workers that have to operate around it. Our order took a good while to be ready so there's opportunity here.

The sheer impressiveness of the burger is enough to make this a 4 stars---but with some caveats on the service. Recommended if you have the chance.

Best burger I've ever had! I love the crispy bits on the edges, while the inside is still juicy and flavourful. There's a perfect amount of rudy sauce - enough to add some zing, but not too much that the burger taste is lost.
The poutine was surprisingly incredible as well - curds were squeaky and gravy was savoury. Better than some poutine-focused places to be perfectly honest.
I don't know what else to say, if you like burgers, you can't not come to Rudy at least once.

editorial_summary.overview: Classic, long-running fast-food chain known for its burgers & fries.

formatted_address: 885 Bloor St W, Toronto, ON M6G 1M4, Canada
name: McDonald's

reviews.text: The woman behind the counter is extraordinary. Twice now she's served me and always polite and speedy. The food was as it should be, fresh and the hashbrown was nice and crispy. Definitely a good way to start the day.
Customer service is not up to the mark. The front guy didn’t even respond to my questions. They are late too

Was given food from the day before ( even tho I supposedly had to wait an extra 20 mins for fresh food). Only know this because of the label saying September 6 617pm and I ordered food on the morning of September 7. Received wrong items then banned from door dash for complaining politely about the order. Will never order from here again obviously for several reasons.

I ordered a grilled chicken sandwich and the lady let me know they had no grilled chicken so I could get the crispy chicken which I didn't want.
So I decided to go with the fish fillet which was more expensive but I like it.
Somehow she ended up giving me the sandwich and change back. 🤷🏻‍♂️

Screw this location. Past midnight you can’t order a combo, it has to be ordered separately. Which charges you an extra 6$. Not a single of the other locations I frequent do this. People work long hours late into the night and sometimes just want to grab a quick meal to go home. NO RESPONSE GIVEN FROM RESTAURANT ABOUT WHY THIS HAPPENS HERE. MANAGER DOESNT CARE TO TELL STAFF WHAT THE REASON IS. MCDONALDS COMPANY WILL NOT COMPENSATE THE DIFFERENCE.

editorial_summary.overview: 2-level sushi house with lunch specials & bento boxes plus takeout & delivery.

formatted_address: 120 Cumberland St, Toronto, ON M5R 1A6, Canada
name: Sushi Inn

reviews.text: Love this Sushi restaurant! It offered a variety and their dragons are the best. Customer service is fast and friendly. Prices are reasonable. Clean and spacious. Prime location but parking may be a challenge.

Good spot if you’re in the mood for sushi in the Yorkville area. Great prices for the portions you are getting. Quick and friendly service as well. Only issue is the tables are quite small (where we sat) and some of the cutlery wasn’t properly cleaned. Otherwise, good spot if you want sushi and don’t mind the busy atmosphere of the restaurant.

I have been coming to Sushi Inn for 28 years. It's one of my fav it's approx $50-$70 per person. It's always fresh and service is amazing. My last visit Rod Stewart was sitting next to me and asked me to order his lunch as  I knew the menu better than he did. Such a humble man. He ordered what we were having, actually.

This place used to be good in the past. Not sure if it’s still run by the same owner but the quality of food is very bad. Let’s just say I have never ever not finished my plate at a sushi place! The salmon was not a good cut. It was chewy. Fried squid was also hard to bite and chewy. There wasn’t much variety on the menu. Well below Yorkville standard.
The price is not really expensive, food was great, I do recommend going there!

editorial_summary.overview: Eatery with a bustling patio & bright, snug interior, serving classic Mexican fare & margaritas.

formatted_address: 277 Augusta Ave, Toronto, ON M5T 2L7, Canada
name: El Trompo

reviews.text: You literally could not get more authentic Mexican food than this. The patio is nice, but I personally enjoy sitting inside - it's like being invited over to eat at a family friend's house than being at a restaurant. Service is friendly, personal and absolutely delightful. Food is fairly priced and generously portioned. I recommend the Jamaica and Horchatta drinks for something light and refreshing. There's nothing negative I can say about my experience here!!
Authentic Mexican food with an absolutely delicious taste! The margaritas were tasty and the tacos were fantastic. I will definitely be back and recommend to others.

Fish tacos are my one true love and el trompo did not disappoint! fresh ingredients and a well balanced taco! Plus their cute patio and drinks make it a great experience. Go early because the patio will fill up fast!

great little spot for food! came in on a saturday afternoon just walking around and was super fast & great service. got the el pastor and mushroom tacos for something small for fuel to walk around but was surprisingly filling. would def recommend trying it out since they had a great menu and amazing service!

I was missing the authentic taste of my home country 🇲🇽, this place was a great find. During the weekends there is live entertainment with a singer/violinist in the afternoon 👏🏼About the food, I started with a choriqueso, then tried tacos al pastor and cochinita tacos, the prices are awesome, the service is super fast, I even tried the flan and some café de olla, everything was delicious. I wish I could have more lemon without having to pay for it.

editorial_summary.overview: Lively, art-decorated outpost for homestyle Mexican cooking along with cocktails & local music acts.

formatted_address: 2848 Dundas St W, Toronto, ON M6P 1Y9, Canada
name: LA REV

reviews.text: Food was good. I found the alcoholic drinks and beer well priced. I went on a Friday night and they had excellent live music (from 7 to 10). Apparently live music is there a few times in the week.

Our experience was hit and miss. I’ll start with the good. The service was really good, the servers were all so nice and friendly. The place is clean. The corn and jalapeño poppers were really good and we would come back just for those.
For mains we got enchiladas and fajitas. They weren’t bad but they weren’t our favourite either. The green sauce with fajitas was very small and everything was a little on the bland side. It didn’t feel worth the price point. The hot sauce helped. Enchiladas were also okay, not bad but not outstanding.

The one strange thing was that the restaurant had a live band and the band came around while we were eating to tell us they had a surcharge (pay as you wish) but it was weird. I’ve never experienced this at any other restaurant with a live band. I’m also not a huge fan of live music so it was strange to pay for something you don’t particularly enjoy.
Other than that, I would come back to try other items on the menu and can recommend the corn and jalapeño poppers, those were really good.
The food was excellent! Friendly staff, everyone was kind and welcoming. The band was also great. Had such a great time.

The food and ambience was lovely, and the cocktails were delicious! The house band was very pleasant and we enjoyed our experience for the most part. The only issue was that we had made a reservation, but the restaurant didn’t tell us they were also hosting a big private party that night, and our table was overrun and surrounded by guests from this party. We had to ask them several times to give us some space. We would have appreciated a heads up from restaurant staff that this was going to happen, or to have been seated somewhere else - our table was right in the thick of it. Our server also seemed to forget about us for long periods of time, so we were stuck there for longer than we wanted.
All this to say we would overall be happy to go back, but now we know to make sure not to go on a night when they have a big group.

I took my wife on a date last night to hear our friends in music, Q&A. We arrived at about 6:15 and found there was limited seating at the bar. Note to self: arrive early when there is Saturday night entertainment. The food was excellent and the jalapeno poppers had my nose happily running for the rest of the evening. All dishes we were served or saw were beautifully presented and the young ladies who were handling service were delightful and very hard on the eyes. Hard to stop looking at, that is. Our one concern was that single folks were nursing beers and taking up the space of 4. Some were slumbering fitfully. Eating at the bar sucked with our backs to either our meal or the music. The only other issue I have is that La Rev's web calendar is blank, so we don't know what is happening in future to further entice us to visit again beyond the beautiful ladies, excellent food, entertainment and welcoming atmosphere. BTW, Dom Dunphy has dumped all over a number of businesses in a totally childish and mean-spirited way. When I invited her to dinner at La Rev at my expense so we could see if she might change her mind, she blew her Karen gasket. Pity she acts so hostile, fearful and nasty.

editorial_summary.overview: Speakeasy-style eatery & bar with an American menu, open mike nights & live-jazz brunches.

formatted_address: 1079 St Clair Ave W, Toronto, ON M6E 1A6, Canada
name: DeSotos Eatery

reviews.text: We weren't supposed to dine in here but so glad we did! The food were delicious and well seasoned. I ordered their penne a la vodka while my partner had ribs. The pasta was so creamy and the portion was huge. I only managed to eat half. I also had some of the ribs and they were so good and tender! The server was really friendly and kind. Love their patio dining. 😊

I loved this place. We went for brunch. They have a small menu for brunch, which kinda put my partner off at first. But I convinced him to give it a try. He tried the burger and I tried the frittata. Omg they were both so delicious. Service was awesome. I loved their Moscow mule. I will definitely be back for both dinner and brunch. Thank you 😇😊🥰

We have been dining here for many years.  Those days are now over.  Ever since Covid, this restaurant has gone steadily downhill.  On our most recent visit we were sat, it took over 15 minutes to get a server to take our order and when they did, they told us it would take one hour to prepare our food.  One hour hamburgers?  We left.  The previous 2 times we went to DeSotos were also terrible service experiences with long waits for service and food.  Avoid this restaurant, especially if you are hungry or have children with you.

Wound up here when another patio said they were full. Glad we did. The Italian food was amazing. Good prices, but alcoholic beverages are a bit on the  expensive side. Would recommend. Staff was friendly and attentive. Chill atmosphere.

For the first time my partner and I had dinner . He ordered the ribs with fries and I had a caesar salad with the grilled calamari.
His dish was cold, fries must have sat for a while and the ribs were dry, hard to swallow. My calamari was good, very tasty but my Caesar salad was room temperature and wilted. The beer we had was not cold.
We did not complain, just made the best it.
Too bad ...we were hoping we found a great little neighborhood place for our dinner nights out.
For sure we will not return.

editorial_summary.overview: 1940s-style diner with jazz-inspired decor, offering breakfast & classic comfort-food dishes.

formatted_address: 249 Victoria St, Toronto, ON M5B 1V8, Canada
name: The Senator

reviews.text:
Came here for brunch with some friends. Service was good and our server was friendly. The mimosas were reasonably priced compared to other places.

The food was decent and they had a decent selection of foods but a bit on the pricier side from what I was expecting.

I wouldn’t mind coming again for sure because it had a cozy vibe to it and overall had a good experience.

We were greeted outside (coincidence, but nice).  Our reservation had been lost, but it wasn't neccessary as there were plenty of empty tables.
Service was excellent.  Staff are eager to make sure everything is exactly how you want it.  The food was good too.  That said, the lamb was requested to be pink/medium but served rare.  It was delicious nonetheless.  The smoked salmon was very fresh.  My guest substituted asparagus for the yam his order would have come with.  It looked wonderful, it cut nicely and the texture was perfect.  My guest was very happy with it until he tasted it.  My guess is the fault was with the asparagus itself because we could find no other fault with it.
Dessert was espresso and a salted chocolate truffle.  A little more salt in the truffle than I like, but still good.  I didn't recognize the region of the coffee used for the espresso, but really liked it too.
I plan to try what looked like an amazing chicken pot pie on my next visit.

We were going to a show nearby. Came across this place by accident. Decided to give it a try. I love the interior, it’s like taking a step back in history. The 3 of us had sliders because we were in a pinch for time. Food was delicious. As we saw the chicken pot pies going to other tables we wished we had of ordered that instead. Smelled delicious as orders were going by our table. Maybe next time.

Went here before a show. Really liked the ambiance, like a diner vibe.
The food is more high end now. Less diner more dinner. I had the steak. It was soooo good!!  It was perfectly tender and melted in my mouth. The garlic butter on the top was excellent! I wish I had more. I got the bowl of fries. When they say a bowl, they mean a BOWL. It was a lot of fries. They were nice, but they would be even better if they had some salt.
I had the chocolate cake for dessert. It was very rich and I enjoyed it. I also tried the apple crumble which was impeccable.
Over all, I loved my dining experience here.

Headline: Eat somewhere else

I went for lunch here recently and was very disappointed. The prices are incredibly high and the quality and portion size of the food do not meet what you'd expect for the cost.

The food was not great and we both left hungry because of how little food you get. We ended up needing to go and eat somewhere else directly afterwards despite spending over $50 for 2 meals here. (Also a cup of coffee is $5!!)

Very disappointed in this restaurant. I would not recommend it. Your stomach and wallet will thank you for eating somewhere else.

editorial_summary.overview: The open kitchen of this relaxed, modern spot serves international fare & brunch on weekends.

formatted_address: 85 Hanna Ave #104, Toronto, ON M6K 3S3, Canada
name: Mildred's Temple Kitchen

reviews.text: We made a reservation  in advance and got our table without any waiting. The staff was a little slow but the food made it up for the delay. The pancakes are a MUST HAVE!! Super soft and fluffy. We also tried their croissant and quiche which were both delicious. Great brunch place. Definitely coming back for the pancakes again :D

Went to try their pancakes and they did not disappoint. They were crispy on the outside and fluffy inside. Overall the dish was too sweet for me (syrup on the plate plus very sweet blueberry topping). You can get the stack of pancakes as a meal or get singles. I would go for a savory dish with a single pancake on the side next time. I have had similar pancakes at another restaurant with syrup on the side and topped with sour cherries, which I preferred. If you like pancakes and sweet toppings you will like these. The grapefruit spritzer was decent, buy didn't feel worth the price.

Was able to get seated quickly without a reservation. Food was delicious! Pancakes are a must-have, but are very sweet so I recommend ordering it as a side (1 pancake vs. 3 as the main).

They did get my order wrong and gave me home fries instead of a salad, but were quick to rectify! Had a full size complimentary salad.

Great spot for brunch but make sure you’re going in as early as possible to get on the waitlist. Over the weekend, the wait is sometimes over an hour because of the popularity. If you are lucky enough to get in, their pancakes are a must try! It’s so fluffy and full over flavour. I usually share this dish with two other people along with a main dish. Grilled cheese was mediocre but the steak and eggs and the croissant dish was really good.

Call them ahead of time to get an expectation of how busy they are!

Absolutely loved it here! We came around 11am on a Saturday and only had to wait an hour (which I think is pretty good for brunch in the city on a weekend!) The wait was worth it - we already knew what we wanted when we sat down so it made everything a lot quicker. The service was awesome and because I was celebrating a birthday they even had a little candle and decoration added to the dessert! We'll definitely be returning :)

editorial_summary.overview: Unpretentious spot pulling 24 taps of craft beer along with burgers, wings & fish & chips.

formatted_address: 500 Queen St E, Toronto, ON M5A 1T9, Canada
name: Dominion Pub and Kitchen

reviews.text:
This place is so beautiful from the inside. I just moved to the area and there aren’t too many near options for brunch, so we decided to give it a try. I ordered the French toast and oh my god, it was delicious and not pricey. My husband ordered the weekend breakfast and it was very tasty, he fell in love with the sausage and the bacon. He only wishes that the portion of the egg was bigger, it seemed like one egg instead of 2. Also, he asked for scrambled eggs and somehow it was runny. The service was good, and could definitely be better. The coffee was great.
The only reason why I am giving 3 stars is because even though our food was amazing we had a hard time enjoying it because of the terrible smoke smell!! What’s up with that?? Are you serious that people are allowed to smoke inside this building?. Can someone explain? I would love to come back with my daughter because she is a fan of French toast, but I am sure she will not tolerate being here for more than 5min. Hopefully they will fix this problem.

Good place to hangout!
The beer and food was decent & good portions. They also have small dish options with cheaper prices, which is a big plus. I really love the atmosphere and all the decor there, looks super cozy and relaxing!!
The Dominion, just off Queen street was a great discovery. Outdoor patio eating, smiling staff and good food reasonably priced. The wine menu was great and the food even better. Thank you Dominion.

Food was entirely cooked to perfection. Calamari was melt-in-your-mouth tender. The blackened fish sandwich was perfectly cooked - a soft, flavourful, thick piece of haddock with a sauce that complimented but didn't overwhelm. The wings were crunchy, even though they were thoroughly coated in sauce.

The drink menu is extensive and extremely varied. Will definitely be back!

Came here for the taste testing menu. Look at the size of the beef patty for the burger, it’s hardly half the size of the bun. The cauliflower bites are dunked/marinated in so much sauce it’s overbearing, the sangria pitcher is only 2 glasses worth and all the fruits are under a bunch of ice so you can’t get them. The cake was good, and service was fine. Do not recommend this place.

editorial_summary.overview: Chic, upmarket Italian place featuring elevated Italian cuisine & an expansive wine list.

formatted_address: 101 College St, Toronto, ON M5G 1L7, Canada
name: Mercatto

reviews.text: We came to Mercatto for a graduation dinner and didn't have the best experience. I wanted to love it but the mains took a long time to arrive, and were only warm when we got them. Some of our party members said their food tasted like it was a day old and it was microwaved. I ordered the sweetened iced tea and lemonade, and it tasted like water with mint. The highlights were the appetizers that we got. The calamari breading was crispy and seasoned well. The fries with truffle crema were great. The service was not good though. Our server didn't ask us how we were doing once the entire meal, or ask if we wanted refills. We had to call him over to order dessert because he didn't come back to the table after we asked for the dessert menus. I saw another patron walk up to him to ask him to attend to their table because he was also ignoring them. I wouldn't go back or recommend this location to anyone.

Lovely space! This beautiful Italian restaurant is located at the MaRS building on the ground floor facing College Street, near University Avenue. It's a very busy location. Miraculously, they were able to seat our large party of 14, out on their patio. Not the most comfortable seating, as we sat on picnic tables. But that was all that was available on a Monday at start of lunch rush. Staff were always courtesy and great under pressure. But do note that it's slow at that time, so plan for enough time, if going during a work day. Individual washrooms are available. Seating is very tight. Not all staff were masked.

Food was good: enjoyed a fresh lemonade and Ricotta Agnolotti.

Quaint Italian restaurant with a great selection of pasta, pizza and traditional Italian dishes and appetizers. Was a huge fan of the cocktails to with the basil spritz the perfect drink for their sizeable yet intimate patio. My recommendation ordering the pepperoni pizza with any of their pastas

Came here for lunch with a colleague today and we were in and out within 35 mins! Our server brought us water immediately upon seating us and when we mentioned we were in a bit of a hurry she guaranteed that we would be out on time (and she was right!).

Pictured below is the prosciutto pizza and the carbonera pasta🍕 🍝 We also ordered the calamari appetizer however I accidently took a video and not a photo, so unfortunately it's not shown in this review. The calamari was tasty, however the portion size was quite small. The pasta was also delicious, however was quite a small portion. The pizza however was great! 👌

Our food was ordered and consumed within 40 minutes so that was an added bonus.

Good location, clean and modern interior, and friendly staff.

I really wanted to love this place but based on my experience, the reviews are quite misleading. I had their Margherita pizza and a glass of Prosecco. Let me just say I have never had a soggier pizza. The sauce was all over the place, the slice can’t even hold, the cheese wasn’t the best. The service, however, was decent and the waitress was attentive and lovely. However, the food was nowhere as good. I understand this can be a convenient business lunch place, however, it’s definitely not the best Italian food in the city. Overall, wouldn’t be back.

editorial_summary.overview: Delivery/carryout chain offering a wide range of pizzas & a variety of other dishes & sides.

formatted_address: 936 Bathurst St, Toronto, ON M5R 3G5, Canada
name: Domino's Pizza

reviews.text: Whenever I order this location  the pizza is usually great, but It was the 50% off week and this time  the pizza came cool. However, they made things right by offering a free pizza. I will definitely be ordering from this location again
Ordered a large pepperoni pizza on the app and the got the order done within 10 minutes. Very impressed.

I order from this Dominos all the time. At least once a week, I’ll never order again. The pizza I ordered was swimming in sauce, it oozed out of every bite. I called to explain that this pizza was made much differently than what I’m use to, that they used way more sauce than normal. They put me on hold - When he returned he told me that no, they used the same amount of sauce and it was made right. Terrible customer service - If you work at a franchise there should be a level of consistency. I’d suggest for anyone to walk right past this location as the quality is terrible and the customer service is worse.

I ordered an extra marinara sauce with my order of cheesy bread when I called for pick up. When he handed me the box, I asked him if the extra dipping sauce was inside - which he opened it slightly, but verified there was two marinaras inside. When I come home, I find there’s only one .. I asked for it over the phone and expecting to pay for it - so he was either too lazy to charge me and lied, or he just straight up lied … it’s just a dipping sauce but super disappointing when I realized after getting all the way home.

Thursday, august 4th (11:15pm)

Ordered from this location once last year; they got our order wrong but after a couple months I figured I’d give them another fair shot.

Both the Chocolate Lava Crunch Cakes were covered in MOLD (pictured below). Disgusting.

One of my two pizzas was completely incorrect (edited in red and as shown in my emailed receipt).

Lastly, unlike Pizza Pizza which abides by the “40 minutes or less” rule, my delivery took a little over 50 minutes.

$50+ wasted. Y’all lost a customer!

editorial_summary.overview: Cozy spot with Neapolitan-style pies cooked in a wood-fired pizza oven, plus pastas, beer & wine.

formatted_address: 240 Annette St, Toronto, ON M6P 1R1, Canada
name: Annette Food Market

reviews.text: Had a wonderful experience here. Very cozy restaurant with great service. It took some time for them to attend to us at the door but understandable since they were quite busy. It definitely helps to reserve a table! I love restaurants with a one page menu.. and even then it was hard to choose with all the good selections. I ordered the arancini for apps which was excellent. I ordered the Potato pizza and I loved it with some chili oil. My friend ordered Linguine ai Frutti di Mare which he really enjoyed. The Lemon Cheesecake was amazing! Not too sweet and I love the passionfruit coulis with it. Honestly I would come back no doubt!

4. The ambiance of Anette Food Market is great- it’s warmly lit, intimate, and vibrant. The menu is extensive with classic Italian favourites and great specials. I always order olives when they’re on a menu- they were particularly yummy! Also ordered the Brussel sprouts, the Ragu, and the pasta special (which was a mushroom pasta). Everything was really good except the service. We didn’t get drinks and our server seemed angry at us for it. They really stopped checking in on our table after clearing our plates- had to go up to the bar to pay our bill. Really enjoyed the food so I will return to try again but didn’t love the service.

Annette Food Market is always our go to for a nice meal in the neighbourhood. Food is always of high quality and this last trip was no different. We ordered their eggplant parm which is still one of the best we've had. Crunchy and layered, its a guilty pleasure. A surprise for us was the shaved asparagus pappardelle which had a lighter flavor on a pea puree. Very delicious as well. Not shown are the pizza and the kale salad as both were gobbled up before I considered taking photos of the meal. Our server was fantastic and had great drink recommendations. The atmosphere was warm and cozy for our first return to in restaurant dining since the pandemic started.

Hadn't been here in years and went with a friend two weekends ago (had a reso).  Service was incredibly quick and we ordered the cesare salad, the mushroom pasta (it was a special) and a pizza - both were amazing.  Definitely would go back!

Food was delicious, drinks were very fancy and service was great. Patio let you people watch and feel the heartbeat of he neighbourhood. I’d recommend this place as a good restaurant to catch up with friends over a delicious meal.

editorial_summary.overview: Bright cafe famous for top-shelf coffees serving European fare from fruit-topped waffles to pizza.

formatted_address: 672 Dupont St #102, Toronto, ON M6G 1Z6, Canada
name: Faema Caffe

reviews.text:
Faema Caffe is located in the building occupied by Faema, a company specializing in selling and servicing serious Italian-made espresso machines and coffee makers, mostly commercial, as well as other restaurant equipment, again with an emphasis on Italian culinary products (pasta, gelato, etc.), a building situated on Dupont St, between Seaton Village and Christie Pits (of the riots infamy).
The coffee is great, the selection of pastries is very good, the service is friendly. The dining area is very spacious, one can leisurely spend hours there sipping cappuccino and feasting on freshly baked croissants, muffins, danishes, biscottis, and other pastries and tea cakes.
The prices are very budget-friendly, with most of the pastries not going over $3 and the most expensive coffee (mocaccino or caffè mocha) is priced at $4.75 got a large cup.
The free WiFi is offered (the password is abcde12345).
The parking lot is adjacent to the cafe, however, due to the commercial nature of the building, to get a parking spot during peak hours could be a challenge.
Don't try to find any details on the company's website; it is only intended for the espresso and restaurant equipment, the cafe domain is for sale.
Love the food! Egg n steak, bacon omelette were really tasty, but not the coffee. The Italian Coffee was strong but didn’t have the rich flavour just bitter and too creamy too.

Nice cafe with beautiful decor and very high ceilings. Great selection of desserts 🍨 and ice cream. 😋 Faema ☕️. Clean 🚽. Always had great service at this location.

Lots of free parking. Wheelchair accessible entrance and wheelchair accessible store.

TorontoLocalGuide review.
It was an ok lunch. Good but nothing special. The cured meat in the sandwich was cut a bit thick so it took a little chewing to get through.

Awesome customer service! ask for Celine. She's the best!! they were listening to our questions. We are really excited to receive our new espresso machine. Thank you again for everything. Completely would do business again with them

editorial_summary.overview: Relaxed, contemporary restaurant serving Thai & Malaysian dishes, plus beer & wine.

formatted_address: 243 Carlton St., Toronto, ON M5A 2L2, Canada
name: Thai Room - Cabbagetown

reviews.text: Food was good here! The presentation has improved a lot! The pad Thai was decent this time around. It was a bit more sour then expected, I believe they had put too much tamarind in this one. Used to be just perfect! If you got one with the right amount of sauce, you got some good pad Thai 🙏🏼

The food used to taste better before. Not sure if they went through management/chef change but it doesn't have the authentic Thai taste anymore. Ambiance is nice. Watch out not to tip twice, the bill already includes a 20% gratuity but the machine still prompts for a tip!
I had 3 different kinds of fried rice here twice - chicken, egg and vegetables. All 3 are really tasty. Takes me back to street food in India. Scrumptious and look great too. Highly recommend.

Good value and tasty food. Thank you Thai room for delivering delicious food.
Edited review : again we got hot delicious vegan food delivered home.

WARNING ! : ketchup in the padthai

The “traditional” pad thai is “tomato based” as described by the worker, it tastes like ketchup and noodles😂. This is a joke, I just ordered for the 2 for 1 deal and the portions are good, the quality however is lacking. I did not pay 30 bucks for some noodles and ketchup I don’t recommend.

editorial_summary.overview: Health-minded, counter-serve chain offering tossed-to-order salads plus soups, burritos & more.

formatted_address: 85 Hanna Ave #104a, Toronto, ON M6K 3S3, Canada
name: Freshii

reviews.text: Sadly this location has gone significantly downhill. I got a salad there tonight and the avocado was inedible, along with lots of the lettuce being slimy and rusty. I also got about halfway through the bit that was edible before realizing the chicken tasted funky… not a great realization at 35 weeks pregnant. Will not return.

This is a disgrace to the freshii name. Terrible quality control. I took my family out here, as I was personally a freshii fan. My brother's food had zero chicken and minimal sauce. There was no care with the order prep. I am never going to order freshii again, especially at this location. Avoid it at all costs.
It's not really my go to place but good for a quick bite with a selection. Lots of competition in the area for salad bowls and with the recent buyout of the brand, I hope it gets better.
I had a great experience here, the staff was nice and friendly, the food is tasty 😋, fresh and good quality.  However, it's a 4 star since the prices of the food are high.

EDIT: tried this location again and yet again it’s not what I ordered. I ordered it with marinated tofu steak and I get it and it’s made with quinoa and. No tofu...

Not terrible but not great. I always get the Oaxaca bowl and this one is not it. There are no Wonton Crips and the portion size is basically cut in half.

editorial_summary.overview: Branch of a chain featuring Louisiana-style spicy fried chicken & side dishes like red beans & rice.

formatted_address: 273 Yonge St, Toronto, ON M5B 1N8, Canada
name: Popeyes Louisiana Kitchen

reviews.text:
Ordered a bunch of spicy chicken tenders.  They made a fresh batch and it was absolutely delicious!  This is way better than rippin' chicken, or the chicken sandwich!  Eat them right away in the restaurant and you are definitely going to be satisfied.
Didn't get a combo.  Don't care about their fries.  Popeye's isn't known for fries... their specialty is chicken!  THIS is by far the best fried chicken!!!  Not even greasy.  Just perfect!

Ordered a 4pc with two sides. I ordered both sides a fries. Turns out I got a 4pc with two half sides. Seriously, potatoes are a dime a dozen. The chicken was cooked at to hot of temperature. Rock hard skin with rubbery chicken. A waste of $15

This location definitely has seen a lot. They can’t control who access the premises all hours of the day. We walked in close to mid night on a weekend and it was busy! Lots of garbage everywhere, garbage overflowing, staff being yelled at, the drink area was being occupied by individuals who were just trying each drink and were spilling everything.

I witness staff asking people to leave as they were sitting in the chairs holding drug paraphernalia.

The upstairs was much more calm but the line up for the bathroom was long.

Our drinks were flat but we didn’t bother complaining the food was ok!

This Popeyes is very busy and they have a lot of good fried chicken here.

We came here on a Sunday at lunch and we ordered the nine piece meal and it was a lot and the portions were huge.

The chicken was good and hot. The onion rings were good and the coleslaw was decent.

This Popeyes is a decent one and we will comeback.
Ordered large onion rings and i received soggy half cooked item. Coating falling from every ring. AND a girl from front desk was so rude

editorial_summary.overview: Retro-style diner serving all-day breakfasts, burgers, sandwiches & bottomless cups of coffee.

formatted_address: 1238 Bloor St W, Toronto, ON M6H 1N3, Canada
name: Duffy's Tavern

reviews.text: Had The daily special for lunch: jerk chicken on the bone with rice and coleslaw. Everything was perfect. Rice and beans perfect, coleslaw delicious and the jerk was moist and well seasoned. Service is always awesome. World cup was on, it was a great crowd.

Duffy's is an incredibly well-laid-out pub. The front nook is good for small groups who want to sit at tables. The bar is spacious and has a few booths behind it to create a great vibe - especially during Raptors games. A few steps down and to the back is the live music space, which is just right for an open mike or up-and-coming act.

Also, the "house lager" is cheap and crushable.

Local pub. Gets the job done. Don’t come in expecting too much but general friendliness and basic but consistent and also bang for the buck. Service is great and realistic. Get the house beer and wings with fries!  Check out the live music and see other neighbours  frequently in this local classic pub! Don’t review this place like a fine dining restaurant ;)

I really liked the food the 6 times I came here (mostly for takeout), I'll most likely stop by for a pound of wings again soon!

+: It's convenient and has great food.
-: Frequent sketchy customers, constantly changing / unreliable hours of operation, and on two occasions they were out of several items on the menu

A true long-time local fixture, friendly staff, always open when you need a beer or a quick bite. The food aint gourmet but it's better than you might expect for a place like this. There are trendier places on the block but Duffy's should never be forgotten!

editorial_summary.overview: Japanese seafood option with a varied menu, adventurous presentations & comfortable decor.

formatted_address: 414 Queen St W, Toronto, ON M5V 2A7, Canada
name: To-Ne Sushi

reviews.text: Awesome sushi, great ambiance, fast service, and very friendly staff. It was delicious sushi and hand rolls. I forgot to take a picture of couple of dishes we ordered 😅 Definitely will go back and also order take out their trays.

I haven’t had sushi in a very long time and we decided to come here for our last meal out before the lockdown happened again.

one thing i really liked about this restaurant was that the QR code on the table opened the menu which allowed you to place your order directly. Made things quite efficient.

I ordered the green salad, miso soup, salmon lovers and the cucumber wrapped roll.

I shouldn’t have ordered the cucumber rolls (they were delicious but it was too much food for me.)

My friend had the sushi and rocky mountain rolls - really enjoyed the coconut flakes on the roll, definitely added a different flavour and texture to the rolls.

I’ll definitely return here!
To-Ne has very homey vibes and I like that you can make resos ahead of time. The food tastes good and they have a lot of variety of food. We got one the mixed platters and sashimi, they were great!

The fish was fresh and tasty. They had run out of rice and first said they would make it with brown rice but then just did the regular rice but less without asking, which was weird, but I'm not complaining. However, the portions were tiny considering the price, and I expected higher quality and quantity for these prices.
Amazing sushi. Place was quiet and clean, staff was super friendly, food was AMAZING. And price was reasonable, my new fac place in town :)

editorial_summary.overview: Chic eatery inside Holt Renfrew serving gourmet salads, sandwiches & sweets, plus drinks.

formatted_address: 50 Bloor St W, Toronto, ON M4W 1A1, Canada
name: Holts Café | Contemporary Canadian Cuisine

reviews.text: Had a nice Sunday brunch with my family here. The interior is beautiful and simple, service was good and efficient, and the food was not bad, but also not the best. I did enjoy my chicken and waffles.. we also loved the pancakes and the smoked salmon was nice and fresh from the bennies. The homefries were a tad bit dry and underseasoned. There was a good variety of items on the menu and all decently priced. A nice place to sit after a day of shopping though that's for sure.
The BLT salad was okay, but it was presented in an interesting manner! Never seen so much lettuce on one plate. Staff was super friendly and accommodating to last minute walk-ins.

As always the service was very quick and efficient. Diners were well socially distanced. No one was sitting at the bar, only tables.

The new decor is open and bright with rich touches here and there.

The food was great. Not a fan of the ricotta (made in house), but the rest of the salad was amazing. Perfect for an afternoon brunch.

Haven’t had a mixed drink I didn’t like here. Their bar staff is always quiet imaginative and forward thinking.

When you need to take a break from shopping at Holt Renfrew this is the perfect place to relax. They had a lovely afternoon tea but unfortunately, I wasn’t able to experience it this time. We came in excited about the mimosa which was introduced to us at $10 which we thought was amazing! But then the server came back to say they ran out of ingredients and that the only options were cocktails at $18. We weren’t too happy with that. After about 30 mins or so, she finally came back to offer the same price for another cocktail. Changed my mind about the whole experience and so we were very pleased with their ability to offer a solution. We ordered the pancakes which were absolutely devine - fluffy, tasty ricotta cheese with light cream and blueberry sauce. Yummy! Will come back another time.

Thank you for a wonderful dining experience.  My parents who are visiting from the UK had such a lovely time and felt very special. Simon, our waiter, was friendly, personable and professional. The food and beverage products were fantastic, well presented and very tasty. The decor is stunning too! Thank you to everyone at Holt's Cafe for a brilliant lunch! I highly recommend! Cheers!

editorial_summary.overview: Offering popular Italian fare & a lengthy wine list in a 3-level venue with modern rustic decor.

formatted_address: 133 Yorkville Ave, Toronto, ON M5R 1C4, Canada
name: Cibo Wine Bar Yorkville

reviews.text: We as a family had the best experience at Cibo at New Year’s Eve. Not only the food was good but the staff is exceptionally good. The best place to be to feel comfortable and cozy while enjoying great Italian cuisine. On a wonderful note my 6 year old decided to write a not to the chef that everything was so yummy. The server (Roberto) held his hand and took him to the chef. To my surprise the head chef himself came to our table , thanked us for our Son’s gesture and gave us too many desserts to enjoy 😊 we felt so honoured. Thank you team Cibo for your great hospitality. 😍🤩🤩

This particular location has been home to a number of restaurants over the years, and I've always liked the space, with multiple levels of seating, big windows, as well as indoor and outdoor seating. We chose this for an outing with extended family because of the proximity to where they were staying, but also because the spaciousness of the restaurant would be ideal for having little children in tow. The menu also has decent variety, so there's something for everyone. We ordered salad, pizzas, and pastas, and everything was good. Service was friendly, though there were a few large groups, so perhaps it did get chaotic for our server at times. As a note, larger groups have 18% gratuity automatically added and had to be on one bill (both requirements not unusual for many restaurants), and you need to leave a credit card number for reservations.

We wanted to grab a quick bite to eat, with tons of options nearby, we chose Cibo.  Both guests from our party had dietary restrictions, so it was a bit of a mission trying to figure out what to order.  But our waiter was patient and very helpful making sure we got some stuff that was dairy and meat free.

Service was great, food was very good.

Our second time there. Great environment. What would make it perfect is to bring out food that resembles logical order. I ordered the breakfast set -- fried eggs with pork chops and udon noodle soup. I didn't get the soup until the very end (we got our two appetizers and my wife got her meal set). We finished eating everything and we had to ask when the soup would come.

Had a great time at Cibo. Server was attentive and the food arrived very quickly. The seating area did feel a little crammed together during lunch, I assume they open the seating downstairs for dinner when it's busy. Would have liked the option to be seated at a larger table downstairs so we are not all struggling to manage the plates and glassware at the table.

editorial_summary.overview: Grant van Gameron's Spanish pinxtos bar features Gaudi-esque wood panels & a Barcelona feel.

formatted_address: 505 College St, Toronto, ON M6J 2J3, Canada
name: Bar Raval

reviews.text:
Came here because I heard good thing about their cocktail but honestly I’ve had better at many other places in Toronto.
Food was nicely presented. Above average tapas but nothing too impressive. We sat on the patio so didn’t have the chance to check the interiors. Would come back again to try other food and drinks. One star less because our server. She might be new? Not sure… interrupted me a few times when we were placing our order. Absolutely no eye contact the entire time.

A cozy tapas bar with a simple and incredible menu. We only ordered a few dishes and from what we tried I am very confident no matter what you order the food will be exquisite.
The vibe is cozy and welcoming which is perfect for a date night or being out with a group of friends.

Great little place for amazing cocktails and fancy finger food and tapas/small plates.
Went there for brunch/lunch.
Their coffee was surprisingly good as well, lol!
We tried:
Tomato toast - 4/5
Coffee - 5/5
Old fashioned cocktail- 4/5
Mushroom with red sauce appetizer- 4.5/5
Eggplant+honey - 4/5

Just here to add another and well deserved 5 star

I came here because of an Eater article and I'm so glad I did! I was sitting at the bar, lucky enough to have Hailey bartend for me and she made some great drinks!

Loved everything about this place the energy was fantastic, the people were wonderful, and the food/drinks were great!

The zucchini and black cod dish was just FANTASTIC. A great balance of flavors and a beautiful amount of black pepper on top.

Hailey was a highlight, she made awesome drinks, pointed me in the right direction food wise, and went above and beyond to talk to me while still working.

Can't recommend this place enough, especially on a warm day!

Fancy little place with warm lightings on college street, Toronto.

tapas/small food plates was well presented and tasted good but nothing too impressive for the high price. We sat on the patio so didn’t check the interiors. The bar looked quite busy and our server was very friendly.
May come back again for another
experience as we had a great time with great company.

editorial_summary.overview: Casual counter-serve chain for build-your-own sandwiches & salads, with health-conscious options.

formatted_address: 1207-1209 King St W Unit 1, Toronto, ON M6K 1G2, Canada
name: Subway

reviews.text: Just paid for a tasteless sub with day old bread. I live in the area and won't eat at this location again until they start caring about the quality they're putting out. Would not recommend this location.

Maybe whoever was working tonight (Sept 26 around 9:45pm) is completely illiterate, but all 3 subs I ordered were not even in the realm of correct. Forgot the chicken on the chicken sub, toppings, dressing, etc were completely ignored and I received whatever the dude felt like giving me. If you own this franchise location you should be brutally embarrassed. BTW the attached picture is the "chicken" sub. Extremely depressing to think people care this little about what they do.

Edit: they refused to refund me. Enjoy your bank dispute, criminals.

Service and sandwich were lovely, however PLEASE NOTE that if you tip on the debit machine, it does NOT go to your sandwich artist.

I was told this after I paid, and if this is true I must say that this is completely unfair and backwards and should be corrected immediately. If you are only paying your staff minimum wage, what gives you the right to take their tips too? Please resolve this.
Clean, most ingredients seemed fresh. 4 stars because you can fill up for cheap if you need to (but, really, not as cheap as cooking your own stuff).

I get it, it's fast food. I'm not expecting fine dining. That said, this location specifically puts so much emphasis on speed it seems like all they care about is getting people in and out at the expense of just slapping the sandwich together. It would be nice if they spent just a little more time with putting everything together.

Don't get me wrong, I'll be eating there again, I just think they could do better.

editorial_summary.overview: This snug, no-frills neighbourhood Chinese eatery boasts an open kitchen & traditional dishes.

formatted_address: 1572 Bloor St W, Toronto, ON M6P 2B2, Canada
name: China Island

reviews.text: Family-run restaurant, very cozy and friendly atmosphere. We always order chicken fried rice, hot and sour soup. After 6 PM, street parking is free. Feel comfortable to tell the owners your preference of tastes. They can satisfy your appetites.

Terrific food.   A flavourful interpretation of Canadian Chinese cuisine.  I highly recommend.

We had a pepper and onion beef dish that was super satisfying.   The egg rolls ( spring rolls ) have the perfect filling.

Service is down to earth and very friendly - a wonderful welcoming experience.

We lan to return often.

Came here for lunch , and they have an amazing deal for lunch. $8.99 for a selection of food (there was 10 items to choose from), which all comes with soup, egg rolls, and rice. I wasn't a big fan of the rice but everything else was superb. The workers were friendly and very kind.

Ordered take out dinner for 2. Beef with vegetables and Kung Pao chicken. The meat was almost non existent compared to the amount of vegetables. Seeing all the good reviews, maybe this was just a bad night
Ppl want to talk down Chinese food. I had a good spot. Since I moved into the neighborhood I will say this is BY FAR the best Chinese food ever!!!!

editorial_summary.overview: Casual counter-serve chain for build-your-own sandwiches & salads, with health-conscious options.

formatted_address: Concourse Level, 333 Bay St., Toronto, ON M5H 2R2, Canada
name: Subway

reviews.text: When the weather gets colder, Subway has a soup of the day.   I enjoy ordering a soup with my sub and sometimes dunk my sub in the soup.   The sandwich artist Jocelyn at this location made me an awesome chicken soup. - I eat Subway everyday reviewer  A Richard Trus Review

Not the best Subway I've ever seen. I like the crew and they were definitely try to make my sandwich as I order. It seems they don't have some ingredients (like avocado). The sandwich was fine anyway.

Honorable service and they have very weird guy working there. i will post some videos on you-tube. i sow  how he attacked the other people. many other places to buy a descent food without getting hassled.
Big queue during 12 Noon to 2 PM. Located in office area. Staff is good. Clean.  You will not going to find seats (during lunch break), to eat so just take away your food and eat at your place.
very, very lousy customer service, this guy never give receipt. what is his problem? if you ask for it, he starts fight.

editorial_summary.overview: Branch of a chain featuring Louisiana-style spicy fried chicken & side dishes like red beans & rice.

formatted_address: 273 Yonge St, Toronto, ON M5B 1N8, Canada
name: Popeyes Louisiana Kitchen

reviews.text:
