Ordered a bunch of spicy chicken tenders.  They made a fresh batch and it was absolutely delicious!  This is way better than rippin' chicken, or the chicken sandwich!  Eat them right away in the restaurant and you are definitely going to be satisfied.
Didn't get a combo.  Don't care about their fries.  Popeye's isn't known for fries... their specialty is chicken!  THIS is by far the best fried chicken!!!  Not even greasy.  Just perfect!

Ordered a 4pc with two sides. I ordered both sides a fries. Turns out I got a 4pc with two half sides. Seriously, potatoes are a dime a dozen. The chicken was cooked at to hot of temperature. Rock hard skin with rubbery chicken. A waste of $15

This location definitely has seen a lot. They can’t control who access the premises all hours of the day. We walked in close to mid night on a weekend and it was busy! Lots of garbage everywhere, garbage overflowing, staff being yelled at, the drink area was being occupied by individuals who were just trying each drink and were spilling everything.

I witness staff asking people to leave as they were sitting in the chairs holding drug paraphernalia.

The upstairs was much more calm but the line up for the bathroom was long.

Our drinks were flat but we didn’t bother complaining the food was ok!

This Popeyes is very busy and they have a lot of good fried chicken here.

We came here on a Sunday at lunch and we ordered the nine piece meal and it was a lot and the portions were huge.

The chicken was good and hot. The onion rings were good and the coleslaw was decent.

This Popeyes is a decent one and we will comeback.
Ordered large onion rings and i received soggy half cooked item. Coating falling from every ring. AND a girl from front desk was so rude

editorial_summary.overview: Slices, sandwiches, panzerotti & pies made-to-order in an ageless eatery with simple decor.

formatted_address: 11 Clinton St, Toronto, ON M6J 2N7, Canada
name: Bitondo Pizzeria

reviews.text:
HIDDEN GEM!! THE PIES HERE ARE BETTER THAN ANYTHING I'VE EVER HAD!

The crust is f%&kin amazing and the toppings taste fresh!!

Definitely would recommend order online otherwise you will have to join the wait line in person.

Just tried a slice of pepperoni, I liked how saucy it was, the cheese was also good and just the right amount. The slices are very big. Honestly not amazing though and not sure I would come back for the pizza. Maybe better when you order with more toppings. I would come back to try the panzarotti’s though as I heard they were really good. Bring cash as they don’t take card!
$5 for a double slice is unbeatable in the area. A neighbourhood institution with a nostalgic vibe. Expect to get pepperoni by-the-slice as it's often the only option available.

My actual rating would be 3.5stars:

Fresh pizzas with fresh sauce, cheese, toppings and dough done right in front of you with thin crust, no gimmicks and no fancy/gentrified nonsense. Prices here are very reasonable, especially since it’s downtown Toronto with the ongoing inflation.

I got the small pizza which the chef was generous to make it slightly bigger than the box meant for it. Yes, if you’re looking for “presentation”, that’s some minus points for the pizza getting slightly folded but for me it’s a bonus as I am here to enjoy the food which I just got rewarded more than what I had paid/expected.

I love the crust of the pizza although the sauce and the overall pizza lacked a bit of flavour or ‘kick’ as I would put it. My pizza had onions and green peppers as the toppings, both which could’ve been given a bit more generously but for the price and the freshness of the pizza, I can’t really complain.

However, I am looking forward to trying their panzerottis which seemed to be very popular with the clientele at this family-run Pizzeria. I will be back for the panzerottis but for the pizza, it won’t be something that I will go out of my way for but it definitely deserves to be on my list of spots for pizzas when I’m on a budget in downtown Toronto.

I received a warm and pleasant greeting from a lovely lady behind the counter. I ordered a pepperoni slice which was very fresh and delicious. I ended up taking a medium pizza home!!! I will definitely visit again 😁

editorial_summary.overview: Comfortable bar with black leather banquettes, serving whisky, rum, tequila & signature cocktails.

formatted_address: 16 Trinity St, Toronto, ON M5A 3C4, Canada
name: SpiritHouse Toronto

reviews.text: This is a great place to come for drinks and snacks and is located in the beautiful and historic Distillery District. We recently had a corporate event here and the staff were so accommodating and wonderful. It was a beautiful day to enjoy drinks on their outdoor patio before we had it inside. We were then given an approximately 90 minute long mixology session which was very interactive in nature and greatly enjoyed by all! They have a number of package options and you would have to contact them directly with your own specific details, but our session had instruction of three different classic and unique cocktails with the opportunity for us to participate hands on. The package s do provide snacks as well which is great as there is a lot of drinking involved! This is a great team building experience and great for private events. Highly highly recommended!

One word. LIAM!! Liam made our experience from start to finish one of the best experiences I’ve ever had at a bar in Toronto. He was incredibly knowledgeable, friendly, listened to what we wanted, and did not miss!! Thank you Liam. Y’all should give him a raise! He’s making the experience an immersive one and a kind one at that.
I attended a silent disco (Halloween) party at SpiritHouse and I had a good time. The ambience is good, and the staff are very polite.

Spongebob Menu was great. Get 'em dirty if you're cool.
The Sandy drink beat the Spongebob drink. Total given considering she trained him in Karate. The drink even has the high ground.
Would definitely return.

As someone who's only recently started to experience the amazing atmosphere of cocktail bars around the city, I can say with certainty that none can top the experience I had at the Spirthouse Toronto.

My friend and I were treated to an amazing time and the drinks were brilliant in both there delivery and presentation.

Even more so thanks to our server Chris, he was able to help us celebrate an amazing evening!

editorial_summary.overview: Susur Lee's stylish eatery for creative Asian & French-influenced dishes meant for sharing.

formatted_address: 601 King St W, Toronto, ON M5V 1M5, Canada
name: Lee

reviews.text:
This is a restaurant I've always wanted to try! Luckily I had cousins coming in Toronto and wanted to go to Lee's to celebrate their birthday.

Let me tell you, beginning to end, we were not deceived AT ALL. The quality of service is incredibly amazing, something that I was expecting from this restaurant but they went over my expectations. You don't even notice when their refreshing your plates or refilling your water. We had such an astounding waiter, Conor, he was more than a perfect host. We are glad that we had him serving us. He knew the menu detailed to the bone.

We were a group of 5 and chose to do the "Chef's Choice", I believe that's what its called... We give them a price and they are able to choose your menu. More like a surprise 3 course menu concept. We had so much food that we were all so full at the end that we were scared we wouldn't have any space for dessert. Such a great experience.

We came here after hearing great things about the restaurant. To our excitement this restaurant did not disappoint, everything we had was delicious and I had zero complaints. It's best if you share your food here as opposed to individually getting your own meals, as you can try more dishes. I was skeptical about the Singapore style slaw at first as I'm not a fan of regular slaw but it was amazing! It was fresh and full of flavours, 20 ingredients to be exact. The reviews recommended the cheeseburger spring rolls so we got them and they were definitely worth it as well. I recommend getting the goat cheese tart if you're a fan of olives, cheese and philo pastry because it was delicious as well. The Top Chef curry roasted chicken is a must have, each bite had loads of flavour if you ate it with all the sauces and pineapple too. The servers were very knowledgeable about the food and provided great customer service also. We didn't get the signature sangria so I can't speak to that, but the table beside us did and was complimenting it. I was surprised at the quality in the food because for the same price in many upscale restaurants in Toronto you don't get the same quality in taste. I recommend trying something different on the menu from something you'd normally get at another restaurant because it really is a unique experience. This place is great for a date night! I'd definitely come here again and recommend it for people looking for a unique experience or looking for a restaurant with great food.

Incredible food and drinks that offer a very unique and well-executed take on fusion cuisine.

When ordering, we were given a thorough rundown of the menu by our waiter, however, he went on to talk for a very long time in a manner that felt like a sales pitch. An example of this was him explaining how shared dishes work in unnecessarily extensive detail.

We loved every dish that we ordered. The slaw is a must-have – the presentation was spot on and it tasted fantastic. The other starters we got included the cheeseburger spring rolls which were a really unique idea and tasted great, however, it was a bit watery. The crispy tofu was perfectly seasoned and combined authentic Asian flavours with other more unique flavours that were well executed.

For mains, I'd highly recommend the black cod – the fish was incredibly tender and sweet, pairing well with the sauce and vegetables underneath. We also had the braised beef which was very tender and tasted great with the mushrooms.

It's also worth to try the desserts. The tong yuen were pretty special in stuffing the Chinese dessert with an unconventional hazelnut chocolate inside.

Aside from at the beginning, our waiter was very hospitable and frequently checked up on us. The atmosphere is very lively along with a modern interior that was comfortable to dine in. As a result, is suits a whole variety of different occasions and I'd love to return.

Went to Lee to celebrate my boyfriends bday, the customer service was exceptional. Our favourite is the popular dish, Singaporean salad with 20 ingredients. We got a seasonal alcoholic drink & the Smokey margarita which was both very tasty. We ordered the top chef chicken curry which was the softest chicken we’ve had, the curry was more on the sweet & ginger-y side. We also ordered the fish taco (seasonal), the cheeseburger spring which were both pretty decent compared to the other two dishes we ordered.

Overall, a very good experience! We ended up being really full and maybe would go for 3 dishes next time instead of 4! They even provided a free birthday desert which we really appreciated

My friend and I ate at Lee for Summerlicious. While it was generally good, it wasn’t amazing considering the price. I quite liked the salmon dish and the lobster dish to start. I especially love the Singapore Slaw which is why this is a four star review instead of three.

The servers are great. The patio is decent. I felt that I’ve had curries that were similar in tastiness to the ones at Lee for half the price.

Go and try the slaw!

editorial_summary.overview: Relaxed French bistro with an open kitchen, serving classic dishes alongside long wine & beer lists.

formatted_address: 492 Queen St W, Toronto, ON M5V 2B2, Canada
name: La Palette

reviews.text:
Finally got to try this place out!
The servers are delightful and management is amazing. Gave us great recommendations which we throughly enjoyed.

They do have a break between 4-5 I believe, so get in before or after for food.

Just like Paris, they’ll serve what they have on house so their menu may not always be accurate.

We ordered the beef tartare, duck confit and steak.

Everything came in at a timely manner - the beef tartare was perfectly seasoned and went well with the spreads on the side. The duck confit really came off the bones and was not dry at all. I ordered it with a salad which was dressed with the perfect amount of crunch and sweetness. The steak was cooked jus the way we wanted and came with its own special sauce.

Will definitely come back to try the oysters and mussels.

It was kind of interesting that how only one guy can handle so many things in a restaurant!
When we went inside the bartender asked us if we were there for food or drinks? And he helped us to sit and then gave us recommendations about drinks and at last made the drink for us.

The drink was pretty good though!
We tried Martini and Negroni and they were both very strong.

I liked everything about this place. The atmosphere was very french, the food was good and the service was excellent.
I see myself coming back.
Thank you

This place is such a special part of the neighbourhood. The staff are so knowledgable and passionate about the drink selections they offer, and the food that they make. Even though the menu is a bit more meat oriented, there is still always a good selection for me as a vegetarian (fried camembert and pear compote in the photo). I can't recommend it more highly.

Amazing first time. Food was just fantastic. Got a fun treat with all staff dressed in Halloween costumes. Tartare was special, great Mussels and really great drinks.

Can’t thank staff enough for how much fun we had.

The London guy

editorial_summary.overview: Fast-food chain offering Mexican fare, including design-your-own burritos, tacos & bowls.

formatted_address: 1970 St Clair Ave W Unit 109, Toronto, ON M6N 0A6, Canada
name: Chipotle Mexican Grill

reviews.text: Please don't look so unhappy when making my food and look anoid when my kid takes her time to choose. Don't worry you didn't give us to mach food. Take a day off you deserve it. Smile it helps.

Ordered at around 2pm today and noticed that the cashier who served me gave me a much much smaller portion size on the bowl compared to what nearly everyone else got. The other servers were generous with the orders that they prepared but this one server/cashier made smaller portions for some reason. Kinda disappointing considering what I paid. Would really appreciate if the portion sizes were the same.
Burrito bowl was awesome! Love the quality and quantity. Good job

While I don't have a problem with the staff - they usually make my order per request and neatly, my rating is based on the food itself. For the 2nd time in the last 2 months, I've gotten food poisoning from this place. Generally, I don't have a problem eating Chipotle, however, eating from this place has made me so sick.
I only come here when I want to have a healthier options but I noticed the workers always rush you to choose what you want and the portion of meat they give you go rice is pretty bad.

vicinity: 1970 Saint Clair Avenue West Unit 109, Toronto

formatted_address: 1250 Bay St., Toronto, ON M5R 2A5, Canada
name: Freshii

reviews.text: Got the Pangoa bowl for lunch. All ingredients seemed fresh and tasted great. The sauce they added definitely has a bit of a kick to it, so if you're sensitive to spice I wouldn't recommend it.

This location skimps on the portions. Looking at the recent reviews, it's common practice for them to skimp on the food. You're better off walking to another Freshii location that's 5 mins away on Bloor near Church.

Go to other freshii in the proximity!!!
The quantity of the salad they give is way smaller than normal!!! I’ve ordered fiesta salad with extra kale topping which I’ve had in many other locations too - the quantity disappoints me. Look at the picture - it doesn’t even reach the side line which other stores exceed. COVID is hitting hard on everyone, not just you. Please value your customers and they’ll value you.

Was not impressed by the menu options, also the servers rushed me. The restaurant has good visibility, positioning and potential. Provide a few more simple menu items. Apply more creativity to the food.
Yummy food. Friendly staff. Great prices.

editorial_summary.overview: Homemade Italian specialties & wine served in a warehouse-style cafe with a delicatessen.

name: Terroni Sud Forno Produzione e Spaccio (Spaccio East)

reviews.text:
Dispute the sharply appearance on the outside the interior is actually very neat. More of an industrial vibe.

I’m very happy with the food at this restaurant. Portions are just right so you can indulge in several options and not feel guilty. Salad was very tasty with the right amount of dressing, mushroom pizza was baked to perfection and pasta was outstanding.

Atmosphere is great and they have an in Store grocery/bakery.

Only reason I’m not giving 5 Stars is because hostess had some attitude. Additionally we asked for a larger table because we were doing a working lunch and she said no and refused to move us. Despite it never getting full at the restaurant.

I don’t recommend this restaurant for any business  meetings or larger parties for that reason.

I look forward to returning in the future, I recommend this restaurant for groups of 2-4, great setting for a lunch date.

I tried this place a couple of times and generally like this place. They have many delicious pastries and good quality bread.
They also have a good selection of Italian products.

The reason I gave 3, is because we went there and bought a couple of pastries and drinks. When we wanted to sit in the dining area, although it was completely empty, they said that we cannot and space is only for dining in. We were not informed about this before ordering so we had to go out in -18 and eat outside .

The space is so unique and beautiful. What a great vibe. It feels super trendy and modern and it's like a "if you know you know" kind of resteraunt. The food was super fresh, I heard they make the pasta in house. Our server Laima was fast and accurate, all smiles and very professional. Top notch food. The Ravioli with the braised beef...I could have eaten that all night long. Can't wait to go back and try more items off the menu...and we ordered a bunch as it was!

A must try Italian restaurant in Toronto!
We got the draft beer, calamari, pizza Regina, and seafood pasta.
Special shout-out to our server Joyse!

Draft beer: very light beer and soft texture

Calamari: the fried crust outside was so light and crunchy, the inside was super soft with the perfect seasoning. With drops of lemon,it’s perfect as an appetizer

Pizza Regina: the size of the pizza shocked me, presentation was awesome too, with different kinds of cherry tomatoes, prosciutto and cheese, it is the perfect Friday night pizza:)

Seafood pasta: the pasta is harder I would like (it might be the authentic way to do it but I like my pasta soft)

I love this place! I often stop in to get lunch, pizza, sandwiches etc. and they’re delicious but wow the dinner was excellent.  The calamari fritti had perfect batter that wasn’t greasy. It was light and tasted fresh and the calamari had excellent texture.  The caprese burrata was also very fresh and delicious.  The handmade pasta was soft and lovely. We had the tagliatelle bolognese and the tonnarelli norcina and both were delicious although the tonnarelli was probably the highlight of our meal.  I love the warehouse industrial type of feel to the place too. It’s unique and I’m quite happy this place is in Corktown.  Our server Laura was wonderfully attentive and suggested great wine.  All in all I’d highly recommend this place if you love Italian food !

editorial_summary.overview: Chic eatery inside Holt Renfrew serving gourmet salads, sandwiches & sweets, plus drinks.

formatted_address: 50 Bloor St W, Toronto, ON M4W 1A1, Canada
name: Holts Café | Contemporary Canadian Cuisine

reviews.text: Had a nice Sunday brunch with my family here. The interior is beautiful and simple, service was good and efficient, and the food was not bad, but also not the best. I did enjoy my chicken and waffles.. we also loved the pancakes and the smoked salmon was nice and fresh from the bennies. The homefries were a tad bit dry and underseasoned. There was a good variety of items on the menu and all decently priced. A nice place to sit after a day of shopping though that's for sure.
The BLT salad was okay, but it was presented in an interesting manner! Never seen so much lettuce on one plate. Staff was super friendly and accommodating to last minute walk-ins.

As always the service was very quick and efficient. Diners were well socially distanced. No one was sitting at the bar, only tables.

The new decor is open and bright with rich touches here and there.

The food was great. Not a fan of the ricotta (made in house), but the rest of the salad was amazing. Perfect for an afternoon brunch.

Haven’t had a mixed drink I didn’t like here. Their bar staff is always quiet imaginative and forward thinking.

When you need to take a break from shopping at Holt Renfrew this is the perfect place to relax. They had a lovely afternoon tea but unfortunately, I wasn’t able to experience it this time. We came in excited about the mimosa which was introduced to us at $10 which we thought was amazing! But then the server came back to say they ran out of ingredients and that the only options were cocktails at $18. We weren’t too happy with that. After about 30 mins or so, she finally came back to offer the same price for another cocktail. Changed my mind about the whole experience and so we were very pleased with their ability to offer a solution. We ordered the pancakes which were absolutely devine - fluffy, tasty ricotta cheese with light cream and blueberry sauce. Yummy! Will come back another time.

Thank you for a wonderful dining experience.  My parents who are visiting from the UK had such a lovely time and felt very special. Simon, our waiter, was friendly, personable and professional. The food and beverage products were fantastic, well presented and very tasty. The decor is stunning too! Thank you to everyone at Holt's Cafe for a brilliant lunch! I highly recommend! Cheers!

editorial_summary.overview: Easygoing local chain for fried & grilled cod, halibut & other seafood, plus fresh-cut fries.

formatted_address: 2151 St Clair Ave W, Toronto, ON M6N 1K5, Canada
name: Halibut House Fish and Chips Inc.

reviews.text: Picked up a couple orders of halibut with fries/onion rings and coleslaw  this afternoon for the first time from this restaurant and my wife and I absolutely loved the meals!! We strongly recommend this location for any fish & chips lovers.

Light and crispy batter with super fresh and crispy fries, the fish was sooo delicious and made even more so by the homemade tartar sauce. Huge portions as well and the service was quick and friendly! My cravings were satisfied 😋 I would come back for sure!

Competitive pricing, very friendly staff.  I don't like the neighborhood because of the traffic, but the location has good parking and is relatively easy to find.

Caesar salad was tasty but also a little watery.  Too much of the white crunchy middle part of the lettuce leaf and not enough of the dark green part.

I got 2 pieces of haddock, 1 fry, coleslaw, gravy and salad for $42 with tax.  Very good gravy.

I liked doing business with HH because it's a chain and I've been to other locations and I knew what to expect.

I will definitely be back.

Got the cod special and it was great! The batter was good, not too much and fried crispy. Good portion. Came with fries, which are unsalted, and coleslaw. The slaw was really good, not too creamy and more on the sour size. Will go again for sure! Staff were friendly.

The food was great, but this is another business that caters to online orders more than dine in customers.
Was never asked if I wanted more coffee, how my food was, no service at all once the food was placed on our table.
We left wanting cheesecake and another coffee, but was told they are busy in the back with orders.
I also witnessed a family place their orders and sat waiting for 20 minutes before leaving as there food was never made.
Too many businesses sacrifice dine in guests to online orders and lose in the end.
Will not return to this location.

editorial_summary.overview: Comfort food with Canadian & global wines, plus a lounge fireplace & TV on the Hilton's 2nd floor.

formatted_address: 92 Peter St, Toronto, ON M5V 2G5, Canada
name: Marquis Lounge and Bistro

reviews.text: Great beds and great location. Nice pool, although a bit small. Always seemed to have a free cookie at check in counter. nice touch. Room had spa like shower. very nice for the price.

Hotel is in a great location, parking is convenient, front desk and valet staff are good, rooms are typical.  We had no issue except that prepaid breakfast  with the Fuel up for Free offer is disappointing.  How can you mess up breakfast??  1.  Serve crappy coffee (Starbucks is around the corner) 2. Provide poor service.  ie make sure all serving staff disappear at the same time. Repeatedly run out of juice glasses, etc.  Food was consistently mediocre.  We stayed 4 nights, 1st breakfast was Ok , 2nd became a little painful, 3rd was  the breaking point. 4th was enjoyed elsewhere.Would stay again but no more breakfast.
This was a very comfortable place to stay, and it has a great location in Toronto. I recommend it!
Nice hotel...close to bars and short walk to convention center
I got a deal that included valet parking

editorial_summary.overview: Established restaurant known for its chicken wings & drumsticks coated in spicy house sauce.

formatted_address: 558 College St, Toronto, ON M6G 1B1, Canada
name: Duff's Famous Wings

reviews.text: Ordered for delivery via UberEats. 1 lb equals to eight wings here. The wings were mediocre, slightly dry. The sauces kind of made up for it though, especially the honey garlic! Tbh, the spicy wasn’t hot at all for me personally.. Overall the food was ok, I don’t think it was worth the hype.

Ordered barbecue wings with Uber eats. Price was ok but small portion 1 lb didn’t seem like allot. Sauce did not taste good and wings weren’t fully cooked. Won’t be ordering again. 👎🍗🫤
I can get three times the amount of wings for the price when buying at the grocery store and much better taste.

Duff’s wings held their reputation of serving spicy wings. I went for the medium flavour and honestly it wasn’t so hot for me. Probably because I’m used to really hot spicy food. But overall had a great time enjoying the wings, fries and drinks. The server was really friendly and nice!

Exactly what you want in a wing place. The wings I believe are never frozen, they have a small but reasonable sauce selection and they taste like quality chicken wings. I ate at another wing place in the neighbourhood and it was a joke compared to Duffs. The fries at duffs are great too, definitely getting the large next time. Sauce wise, their slogan “The medium hot is hot” rings true for me. But the step up to hot isn’t massive. Will prolly go full on hot next time.
Great wing spot. Quality sauce, big wings. 100% worth a visit if you like wings. Spicy BBQ is my recommendation

editorial_summary.overview: Laid-back restaurant & sports bar with a wide menu of hearty pub grub, plus draft beers & cocktails.

formatted_address: 157 Roncesvalles Ave, Toronto, ON M6R 2L3, Canada
name: Gabby's - Roncesvalles

reviews.text: I’ve not had such delicious ribs in a long time. Sure, you can go to a place like Hendricks for some great ribs, but Gabby’s was other-worldly. Great beer selection, great prices, and the flavours of the food were heavenly. We ate so much we almost had to roll north of Roncesvalles Avenue to get home 😅
Great place , comfy and friendly staff, amazing wings and ribs, snacks and chips

Joanna was our server, she was super informed on the menu and very friendly and personable. We were visiting from Nova Scotia and had a great experience! Will definitely be back when we're around again.
Shrinkflation has hit the steak sandwich. Thinnest steak ever.  It used to be my go to dish. No more. I will stick to the wings

Omg .. the server tried to refuse my Service Dog .. after I stood in awe for about a minute with my mouth open she was kinda rude asking if I needed specific seating to go with him? .. what the actual ... eff .. he wears a full vest full of patches.. ..

editorial_summary.overview: Popular local chain outpost for falafels, shawarma wraps, combo plates & daily meal deals.

formatted_address: 729 Bloor St W, Toronto, ON M6G 1L5, Canada
name: Ali baba's Middle Eastern Cuisine

reviews.text: Ordered with Uber eats buy 1 get 1 free promotion. Cheaper shawarma option but the price reflects the quality. Taste wasn’t the greatest and meat lacks quality. They still have long way to go for improvement. 😵‍💫😐😑😒👎🥙
Food tasted great! Portion size was good, everything was fresh and prices are reasonable. Staff are very kind and quick. Definitely my go to when I am in Bloor West area.
Disgusting looked like food picked out of a garbage can, ordered  Two chicken schwarmer wraps we got nothing even close to it.

Very horrible portioning! I go to any other ali babas and it'll get double! Service was terrible, they were lost, confused for me trying to get 5 items! And the store was empty so it wasn't even busy. They had their own food which wasn't part of what they sold right on the line with everything else, open for everyone to see! Overall bad experience. Never coming back to this store.

The worst chicken platter ever!
The chicken leg was cold!
The rice was uncooked and I already feel that I got food poisoning.
Stay away of this place.
